        "content": "<!--DOCTYPE html-->\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<title>Top 7 Hidden Historical Gems in Delhi Most Tourists Miss</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<div class=\"container\">\n    <h2>Discovering Delhi's Forgotten Monuments</h2>\n    <p>While the Red Fort and Qutub Minar draw thousands of tourists daily, Delhi's history is so vast that dozens of stunning centuries-old structures remain hidden in plain sight. Visiting these offbeat ruins offers a peaceful, crowd-free glimpse into the dynasties that ruled the city.</p>\n\n    <h3>1. Agrasen ki Baoli</h3>\n    <p>Tucked between the high-rise office blocks of central Delhi, this 14th-century stepwell is an architectural marvel. Featuring 103 stone steps leading down to a dry reservoir, it is incredibly photogenic and holds an aura of mystery.</p>\n\n    <h3>2. Mirza Ghalib's Haveli</h3>\n    <p>Located in the labyrinth of Ballimaran, Old Delhi, this was the residence of the famous 19th-century Urdu poet Mirza Ghalib. The structure has been turned into a small memorial museum exhibiting his handwritten poems and letters.</p>\n\n    <h3>3. Jahaz Mahal (Ship Palace)</h3>\n    <p>Situated in Mehrauli, this Lodi-era monument gets its name because its reflection in the adjacent lake resembled a floating ship. It served as a summer retreat for royal families.</p>\n\n    <div class=\"tip-box\">\n        <strong>🗺️ Explorer Pro-Tip</strong>\n        <p>Offbeat sites are scattered across the city. For easy commuting, locate your base in a central area. You can find <a href=\"https://gethotelstays.com\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: var(--accent); font-weight: bold; text-decoration: underline;\">heritage hotel stays in Central Delhi on GetHotelStays</a>, offering smooth transit and maximum safety.</p>\n    </div>\n</div>\n</body>\n</html>",
